description: The Kolkata Knight Riders won their third Indian Premier League title in 2024, defeating Sunrisers Hyderabad in Chennai. Pakistan legend Wasim Akram praised the absence of Team India players in the final as a "blessing in disguise" for Indian cricket, allowing them to focus on their World Cup preparations without the added fatigue of a long tournament.
title: Akram calls absence of India players in IPL final a 'blessing'
Delhi hospital tragedy: Fire dept alerted after 35 minutes

description: A six-year-old girl, Khushi, was tragically mauled to death by stray dogs in Kanpur while trying to save her younger brother, Bhola, from the attack.
title: Stray dogs kill girl trying to save her 2-year-old brother

description: AIMIM's Malegaon unit President Abdul Malik Mohammed Yunus Isa (40) shot at in Malegaon. Condition stable. AIMIM president Asaduddin Owaisi condemns attack. Former Malegaon mayor, previously in Janata Dal, attacked outside hotel.
title: Malegaon chief of AIMIM and ex-mayor shot at, out of danger
Delhi to Varanasi flight evacuated due to bomb threat

description: Kolkata Knight Riders won their third Indian Premier League title in 2024 under Gautam Gambhir's mentorship. Gambhir, who previously led KKR to titles in 2012 and 2014, has been praised for his strategic influence and leadership. Former Sunrisers Hyderabad head coach Tom Moody praised Gambhir's guidance for bringing clarity and stability to the team.
title: 'No rocket science': Ex-players on how Gambhir led KKR to IPL title

description: The recent ICJ ruling did not change Israel's course on military operations in Gaza, met with continued activity. Tanks advancing in Rafah, air strikes causing destruction. Netanyahu's colleagues accuse ICJ of bias. Critics fear Israel's isolation. Limited aid in Gaza, ICJ calls for more action to prevent displacement.
title: ICJ ruling unlikely to change Israel's military strategy in Gaza

description: A rocket launched by North Korea to deploy the country's second spy satellite exploded shortly after liftoff, a setback for leader Kim Jong Un's satellite monitoring plans of the US and South Korea.
title: North Korean rocket carrying its 2nd spy satellite explodes

description: Pope Francis used a derogatory term for the LGBT community during a closed-door meeting with Italian bishops, stating that gay people should not be allowed to become priests.
title: Pope Francis used vulgar Italian word to refer to LGBT people

description: Tornado-spawning thunderstorms in the Southern Plains and Ozark Mountains killed 21 people across four US states. Forecasters warned of more severe weather ahead.
title: US storms kill at least 21 across 4 states on Memorial Day weekend

description: Former cricketer Shahid Afridi has praised Pakistan's bowling line-up as the strongest in the upcoming T20 World Cup, stating that the team's pace attack, including Shaheen Shah Afridi, Abbas Afridi, Mohammad Amir, Naseem Shah, and Haris Rauf, is exceptional in its skill and depth. Pakistan are a favorite for the tournament, following their runner-up finish in the previous edition.
title: T20 WC: Afridi lauds Pakistan's bowling line-up as strongest

description: Tigers in Indian Sundarbans provide alternative livelihoods to villagers in West Bengal, with a rise in tourism activities and tiger sightings over the past decade.
title: Tiger burning brighter in Sundarbans, but villagers are smiling

description: Dumka witnesses a complex political landscape with alliances, defections, and legal implications shaping the upcoming Lok Sabha polls. Local perspectives highlight the community's diverse opinions and loyalties in the midst of the electoral battle between JMM and BJP candidates.
title: ‘Snubbed’ Sita Soren lays claim on Shibu Soren legacy & seat

description: Agnikul Cosmos, a spacetech startup, put on hold the inaugural test launch of its single-stage rocket powered by a semi-cryogenic engine just minutes before lift-off.
title: Agnikul's single-stage tech demo rocket launch put on hold

description: The upcoming elections in Ghazipur feature a showdown between Afzal Ansari and BJP's Parasnath Rai, with political heavyweights like Manoj Sinha and Yogi Adityanath playing significant roles.
title: Don dead but his shadow looms over Ghazipur

description: Former India cricketer Ambati Rayudu has sparked controversy again after he criticized Virat Kohli and Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) after the IPL 2024 final. Rayudu, along with Kevin Pietersen and Mayanti Langer, discussed the impact of a player like Virat Kohli on a team like RCB, despite Kohli's stellar performance.
title: 'Kohli needs to ease his standards': Rayudu stirs controversy again

description: Kalpana Murmu Soren, an engineer with an MBA degree, emerged into the political limelight following her husband Hemant Soren's arrest by the Enforcement Directorate. She transitioned from a private life to becoming a prominent figure in Jharkhand politics.
title: Kalpana goes all out to fill Hemant’s shoes

description: Final-year student Harsh Kumar, son of journalist Ajit Kumar, was beaten to death by masked assailants near Patna Law College. The attackers, 10-15 in number, targeted him with rods and bricks. CCTV footage is being examined to identify the culprits.
title: Patna University student waylaid, killed by masked youths
